The Chronicle Peter Matika, Online Desk The Zimbabwe Energy Regulatory Authority (Zera) has reviewed upwards the price of Liquefied Petroleum (LP Gas). In a statement, the energy regulator noted that it had increased the price of LP gas from US$1.77 or $1 499.85 to US$2.06 or $1 861.35 per kg, effective immediately. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-687507" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-9-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-9.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-9-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zera last reviewed LP gas prices on 8 February this year 